<p>We are "mobilizing" an existing search results page, implemented as a Smarty template.</p>  <p>My developer has already applied the CSS to do the usual reformatting stuff, but we're stumped on how to present the refinements, currently implemented as text links. All the variables exist in the Smarty template like this:</p>  <p><code>{$RefinementEntries[i].FacetNamePublic}</code> gives you the refinement name (for example, "Brand", "Price", etc) </p>  <p>and the line that formats the anchor (a tag purposely omitted) <code>href="http://{$RefinementEntries[i].RefinementEntryItems[j].LinkURL}" title="{$RefinementEntries[i].RefinementEntryItems[j].LinkTitle}" onMouseOver="{$RefinementEntries[i].RefinementEntryItems[j].LinkStatus}" style="font-size:14px;color:black;" class="CSSRefineLink"&gt;{$RefinementEntries[i].RefinementEntryItems[j].LinkText}</code> gives you everything you need to know for each refinement: the link, the link text, etc.</p>  <p>What are our options to display these filters in a mobile friendly way just like amazon does? From reading other threads, JQuery Mobile looks like an option. Is it the only option?</p>